Hey. are you okay?

4
00:01:23.024 --> 00:01:24.203
Yeah.

5
00:01:24.922 --> 00:01:26.438
You need some help?

6
00:01:26.802 --> 00:01:27.926
No.

7
00:01:35.975 --> 00:01:38.258
Annie. what're you doing?

8
00:01:39.013 --> 00:01:40.557
I'm fine. dad.

9
00:01:58.511 --> 00:01:59.821
What's the matter？

10
00:01:59.846 --> 00:02:01.346
What's going on?

11
00:02:08.009 --> 00:02:09.212
Annie?

12
00:03:06.870 --> 00:03:08.113
Dad?

13
00:03:08.944 --> 00:03:10.138
Hey.

14
00:03:10.582 --> 00:03:11.961
I love you.

15
00:03:13.094 --> 00:03:13.947
I know.

16
00:03:14.351 --> 00:03:15.693
I know.

17
00:03:16.520 --> 00:03:18.985
I just want you and mom to
know how much I love...

18
00:03:23.125 --> 00:03:26.472
Dad. I'm sorry that I can be such
a shit to you sometimes.

19
00:03:28.912 --> 00:03:30.646
I don't know why I do that.

20
00:03:35.908 --> 00:03:38.486
Just know that I love you. okay?

21
00:03:40.602 --> 00:03:42.652
I just really love you both.

22
00:05:16.042 --> 00:05:17.418
Hey Jay.

23
00:05:17.904 --> 00:05:19.386
Hey. what's up?

24
00:05:20.017 --> 00:05:22.483
Nothing.
How long you out here?

25
00:05:22.772 --> 00:05:24.690
I'm going to watch a moive.
Do you feel like it?

26
00:05:25.701 --> 00:05:27.102
Actually. I'm going out tonight.

27
00:05:27.835 --> 00:05:29.079
That guy?

28
00:05:30.982 --> 00:05:32.290
I like him.

29
00:05:34.456 --> 00:05:35.677
Me too.

30
00:05:55.446 --> 00:05:56.991
I see you.

31
00:06:50.515 --> 00:06:52.028
What're you reading?

32
00:06:53.030 --> 00:06:54.688
<i>The Idiot</i>
(Fyodor Dostoyevsky）

33
00:06:55.323 --> 00:06:56.993
Is it any good?

34
00:06:57.494 --> 00:06:58.897
I don't know yet.

35
00:06:59.108 --> 00:07:00.676
It's about Paul.

36
00:07:02.071 --> 00:07:03.293
Hey. Jay.

37
00:07:04.319 --> 00:07:05.662
Hey. Paul.

38
00:07:10.303 --> 00:07:11.482
Stop.

39
00:07:12.722 --> 00:07:14.279
Hey. I've an idea.

40
00:07:14.706 --> 00:07:15.898
What?

41
00:07:18.520 --> 00:07:19.952
It got away.

42
00:08:48.311 --> 00:08:50.152
You ever played the 'Trade' game?

43
00:08:51.290 --> 00:08:52.566
No. what is that?

44
00:08:52.598 --> 00:08:54.207
It's a people watching game.

45
00:08:54.265 --> 00:08:56.683
My sister and I used to play
when we were bored.

46
00:08:57.128 --> 00:08:58.739
You're bored right now?

47
00:08:58.898 --> 00:09:00.101
No. shut up.

48
00:09:00.126 --> 00:09:01.555
Let me finish.

49
00:09:02.264 --> 00:09:03.836
Okay. how do you play?

50
00:09:04.624 --> 00:09:06.651
You start by watching the crowd.

51
00:09:06.807 --> 00:09:10.058
Casually.
Just go by the people around you.

52
00:09:10.972 --> 00:09:12.189
Okay.

53
00:09:12.606 --> 00:09:14.268
Now. without telling me.

54
00:09:14.676 --> 00:09:17.091
pick a person you want to
trade places with.

55
00:09:17.116 --> 00:09:20.262
It can be anyone.
for whatever reason.

56
00:09:26.040 --> 00:09:27.558
Okay. I got it.

57
00:09:28.024 --> 00:09:31.382
Now. I get 2 guesses to
figure out who you picked

58
00:09:31.381 --> 00:09:33.560
and why you want to
trade places with them.

59
00:09:34.529 --> 00:09:36.309
Okay. good luck.

60
00:09:42.663 --> 00:09:44.035
That guy.

61
00:09:46.889 --> 00:09:48.115
No.

62
00:09:48.423 --> 00:09:50.665
Okay then.
Who'd you pick?

63
00:09:52.625 --> 00:09:53.839
Him.

64
00:09:55.239 --> 00:09:56.650
The dad?

65
00:09:56.742 --> 00:09:58.089
No. the son.

66
00:09:58.122 --> 00:10:00.302
I mean how cool would that be.
to have your whole life ahead of you?

67
00:10:00.327 --> 00:10:01.548
You know?

68
00:10:01.611 --> 00:10:02.660
Come on.

69
00:10:02.685 --> 00:10:04.826
It's not like you're old.
You're 21.

70
00:10:05.824 --> 00:10:07.380
I know. but...

71
00:10:08.532 --> 00:10:10.750
look at how happy that kid is.

72
00:10:10.842 --> 00:10:14.255
Plus. at that age you could go to
the bathroom any time you want.

73
00:10:14.370 --> 00:10:15.473
Total freedom.

74
00:10:15.498 --> 00:10:16.472
Yeah.

75
00:10:16.511 --> 00:10:18.057
Splashing his shirt right now.

76
00:10:18.082 --> 00:10:21.604
Yeah. Exactly.
I can never get away with that.

77
00:10:26.495 --> 00:10:27.828
Okay. my turn.

78
00:10:29.702 --> 00:10:30.965
Okay.

79
00:10:39.862 --> 00:10:41.044
Okay. got it.

80
00:10:53.438 --> 00:10:55.348
How about the girl in
the yellow dress?

81
00:10:57.326 --> 00:10:58.616
Where?

82
00:10:59.874 --> 00:11:01.289
Right there.

83
00:11:02.219 --> 00:11:03.810
I don't see her.

84
00:11:03.967 --> 00:11:05.373
Right there.

85
00:11:09.697 --> 00:11:11.254
Are you teasing me?

86
00:11:12.552 --> 00:11:14.747
I'm sorry. I just...
I don't...

87
00:11:14.772 --> 00:11:15.997
Can we go?

88
00:11:16.617 --> 00:11:17.831
I'm sorry.
I just have to go.

89
00:11:17.856 --> 00:11:18.359
If you. uh—

90
00:11:18.384 --> 00:11:20.239
Can we — Can we go
back into the car?

91
00:11:21.557 --> 00:11:24.254
Is there someone in there
that made you want to leave?

92
00:11:24.690 --> 00:11:26.584
Like an ex-girlfriend
or something?

93
00:11:26.609 --> 00:11:28.585
You said you saw a
girl in yellow dress.

94
00:11:28.660 --> 00:11:30.304
Is that someone that you knew?

95
00:11:30.482 --> 00:11:34.207
No. I just felt sick.
I feel better being outside.

96
00:12:22.779 --> 00:12:24.542
Thanks for walking with me.

97
00:12:26.015 --> 00:12:27.929
Mom knows you smoke.

98
00:12:28.659 --> 00:12:31.285
Yeah but. she'll cry if
she actually sees it happening.

99
00:12:31.348 --> 00:12:33.783
Or she'll just steal your cigarettes.

100
00:12:35.579 --> 00:12:37.024
How's it going with you?

101
00:12:38.782 --> 00:12:40.081
Good.

102
00:12:40.534 --> 00:12:41.767
Honestly.

103
00:12:42.552 --> 00:12:44.635
I don't know.
He was acting kind of weird last night.

104
00:12:45.805 --> 00:12:46.937
Why?

105
00:12:48.146 --> 00:12:50.436
He said he wasn't feeling well.
but...

106
00:12:50.461 --> 00:12:52.527
it was like something was on his mind.

107
00:12:54.645 --> 00:12:56.196
Have you...?

108
00:12:56.758 --> 00:12:57.661
No.

109
00:12:57.954 --> 00:12:58.702
No.

110
00:12:58.727 --> 00:13:00.714
I know he wants to. but...

111
00:13:02.419 --> 00:13:04.497
I don't know.
He seemed different last night.

112
00:13:11.265 --> 00:13:12.800
Do I smell bad?

113
00:13:13.905 --> 00:13:17.333
Like uh...
Cherry Coke. banana nicotine.

114
00:13:17.550 --> 00:13:18.840
That's my favorite flavor!

115
00:13:18.865 --> 00:13:20.463
I... love it.

116
00:14:47.483 --> 00:14:49.451
Let's go back to the car.

117
00:16:17.335 --> 00:16:18.624
That's funny.

118
00:16:18.649 --> 00:16:21.783
We used to day dream about
being old enough to go on dates.

119
00:16:22.924 --> 00:16:25.448
Driving around with my friends
in their cars.

120
00:16:27.666 --> 00:16:29.801
I had this image of myself.

121
00:16:30.258 --> 00:16:33.267
holding hands with a
really cute guy.

122
00:16:34.425 --> 00:16:36.435
Listening to the radio.

123
00:16:37.309 --> 00:16:39.188
Driving along some pretty road.

124
00:16:39.823 --> 00:16:41.714
Up north maybe.

125
00:16:42.389 --> 00:16:44.896
And the trees start to change colors.

126
00:16:50.144 --> 00:16:52.565
It's never about going anywhere really.

127
00:16:55.805 --> 00:16:58.113
Some sort of freedom I guess.

128
00:17:00.616 --> 00:17:02.497
Never old enough.

129
00:17:02.669 --> 00:17:04.426
The hell do we go?

130
00:18:18.200 --> 00:18:19.480
Jay?

131
00:18:20.712 --> 00:18:22.161
You awake?

132
00:18:26.159 --> 00:18:27.583
I'm sorry.

133
00:18:30.516 --> 00:18:32.176
What are you doing?

134
00:18:38.424 --> 00:18:40.084
I'm not going to hurt you.

135
00:18:40.696 --> 00:18:42.141
Don' t worry.

136
00:18:49.174 --> 00:18:50.964
You're not going to believe me.

137
00:18:52.054 --> 00:18:54.435
But I need you to remember
 what I'm saying.

138
00:18:56.022 --> 00:18:57.265
Okay?

139
00:19:03.133 --> 00:19:04.565
This thing.

140
00:19:06.788 --> 00:19:09.023
It's going to follow you.

141
00:19:14.298 --> 00:19:16.300
Somebody gave it to me.

142
00:19:17.663 --> 00:19:19.546
And I pass it to you.

143
00:19:20.575 --> 00:19:22.259
Back in the car.

144
00:19:24.161 --> 00:19:26.260
It could look like someone you know.

145
00:19:27.396 --> 00:19:29.803
Or it could be a stranger in a crowd.

146
00:19:30.962 --> 00:19:33.480
Whatever helps it to get close to you.

147
00:19:35.027 --> 00:19:37.117
He could look like anyone.

148
00:19:38.306 --> 00:19:40.343
But there is only one of it.

149
00:19:43.714 --> 00:19:45.094
Help.

150
00:19:47.410 --> 00:19:49.007
Help!

151
00:19:49.114 --> 00:19:50.745
And sometimes...

152
00:19:51.066 --> 00:19:52.868
Sometimes I think it looks like...

153
00:19:53.342 --> 00:19:54.548
people you love.

154
00:19:55.546 --> 00:19:56.877
Just to hurt you.

155
00:20:10.665 --> 00:20:12.253
I see it.

156
00:20:12.314 --> 00:20:13.582
I see it.

157
00:20:39.073 --> 00:20:40.663
Who is it?

158
00:20:54.632 --> 00:20:56.496
You can get rid of it. okay?

159
00:20:56.531 --> 00:20:58.830
Just sleep with someone
as soon as you can.

160
00:20:58.861 --> 00:21:00.464
Just pass it along.

161
00:21:00.535 --> 00:21:02.649
If it kills you.
it'll come after me.

162
00:21:02.674 --> 00:21:04.263
Do you understand?

163
00:21:12.023 --> 00:21:13.840
What the fuck do you want?!?

164
00:21:16.682 --> 00:21:19.101
Jay.
I'm doing this to help you.

165
00:21:19.909 --> 00:21:21.725
Just to let you know it's real.

166
00:21:31.400 --> 00:21:32.706
Help!!!

167
00:21:33.005 --> 00:21:34.437
Help me!

168
00:21:48.451 --> 00:21:51.337
Never go into a place that
doesn't have more than one exit.

169
00:21:51.363 --> 00:21:53.352
It's very slow.
but it's not dumb.

170
00:22:09.166 --> 00:22:10.725
Can I have some?

171
00:22:10.952 --> 00:22:12.162
Yeah.

172
00:22:16.750 --> 00:22:18.230
Listen to this:

173
00:22:18.852 --> 00:22:22.048
<i>“I think that if one is faced by
inevitable destruction --</i>

174
00:22:22.163 --> 00:22:24.501
<i> if a house is falling upon you.
for instance --</i>

175
00:22:24.955 --> 00:22:27.776
<i>one must feel a great longing to sit down.</i>

176
00:22:27.863 --> 00:22:30.022
<i>close one's eyes and wait.</i>

177
00:22:30.456 --> 00:22:32.154
<i>come what may . . .”</i>
(Fyodor Dostoyevsky. "The Idiot")

178
00:22:32.617 --> 00:22:34.825
That's why we're drinking on the porch.

179
00:22:37.463 --> 00:22:39.081
Is you mom asleep already?

180
00:22:39.789 --> 00:22:41.432
Almost for sure.

181
00:22:41.766 --> 00:22:43.722
She wakes up at 5:15.

182
00:22:43.884 --> 00:22:45.501
That would kill me.

183
00:22:45.519 --> 00:22:46.631
So...

184
00:22:46.764 --> 00:22:48.233
Where's Jay at?

185
00:22:49.591 --> 00:22:51.040
On a date.

186
00:22:53.351 --> 00:22:54.654
Your turn.

187
00:22:55.028 --> 00:22:56.336
Who is he?

188
00:22:57.029 --> 00:22:58.376
Somebody new.

189
00:22:58.601 --> 00:23:00.004
Of course.

190
00:23:00.049 --> 00:23:02.257
Your sister is so pretty.
It's annoying.

191
00:23:02.344 --> 00:23:03.478
It is annoying.

192
00:23:03.503 --> 00:23:05.059
Anyway. she's nice.

193
00:23:21.393 --> 00:23:22.594
Is everything okay?

194
00:23:31.575 --> 00:23:33.321
Don't let it touch you.

195
00:23:51.883 --> 00:23:52.975
Jay!

196
00:24:16.102 --> 00:24:17.347
What happened?

197
00:24:18.978 --> 00:24:20.202
I don't know.

198
00:24:24.075 --> 00:24:26.205
Those people are such a mess.

199
00:24:33.190 --> 00:24:34.950
It was consensual.

200
00:24:37.765 --> 00:24:38.991
Yeah.

201
00:24:40.756 --> 00:24:43.109
And. you never see the woman before?

202
00:24:46.621 --> 00:24:47.845
No.

203
00:24:48.251 --> 00:24:49.303
Okay.

204
00:24:49.393 --> 00:24:51.238
Have you ever been to his home ?

205
00:24:54.868 --> 00:24:56.649
I know where he live.
but...

206
00:24:57.587 --> 00:24:59.499
I never went inside.

207
00:25:01.744 --> 00:25:03.987
He said he was embarrassed where he lived.

208
00:25:54.098 --> 00:25:55.802
Did she catch anything?

209
00:25:57.514 --> 00:25:59.063
I don't think so.

210
00:25:59.934 --> 00:26:01.818
Ah...
Poor Jamie.

211
00:26:03.704 --> 00:26:07.383
Apparently he used a fake name
to rent a house in the city

212
00:26:07.544 --> 00:26:09.807
The police searched the place.
they can't find him.

213
00:26:09.823 --> 00:26:11.436
Oh my God.

214
00:26:11.867 --> 00:26:14.094
Breaks my heart the things he said to her.

215
00:26:14.333 --> 00:26:16.222
Some weird. sick.

216
00:27:20.969 --> 00:27:23.848
<i> "I should have been a pair of ragged claws</i>

217
00:27:24.416 --> 00:27:27.735
<i>scuttling across floors of silent seas"</i>

218
00:27:29.146 --> 00:27:33.269
<i>And the afternoon. the evening.
sleeps so peacefully.</i>

219
00:27:34.592 --> 00:27:36.864
<i>Smoothed by long fingers.</i>

220
00:27:36.864 --> 00:27:41.313
<i>Asleep … tired … or it malingers.</i>

221
00:27:41.501 --> 00:27:45.448
<i>Stretched out on the floor.
here beside you and me.</i>

222
00:27:45.985 --> 00:27:50.568
<i>Should I. after tea and cakes and ices.</i>

223
00:27:51.332 --> 00:27:54.999
<i>Have the strength to force
the moment to its crisis?</i>

224
00:27:55.545 --> 00:27:58.121
<i>But though I have wept and fasted.</i>

225
00:27:58.452 --> 00:28:00.479
<i> wept and prayed.</i>

226
00:28:01.025 --> 00:28:04.730
<i>Though I have seen my head
(grown slightly bald)</i>

227
00:28:04.826 --> 00:28:06.780
<i>brought in upon a platter.</i>

228
00:28:07.097 --> 00:28:10.286
<i>I am no prophet—
and here’s no great matter;</i>

229
00:28:10.953 --> 00:28:14.300
<i>I have seen the moment
of my greatness flicker.</i>

230
00:28:15.021 --> 00:28:17.859
<i>And I have seen the eternal Footman</i>

231
00:28:18.118 --> 00:28:20.521
<i> hold my coat. and snicker.</i>

232
00:28:21.115 --> 00:28:24.047
<i>And in short. I was afraid.</i>

233
00:28:24.480 --> 00:28:27.854
<i>And would it have been worth it. after all.</i>

234
00:28:28.665 --> 00:28:32.287
<i>After the cups. the marmalade. the tea.</i>

235
00:28:32.825 --> 00:28:37.048
<i>Among the porcelain.
among some talk of you and me.</i>

236
00:28:37.128 --> 00:28:38.903
<i>Would it have been worth while.</i>

237
00:28:38.928 --> 00:28:41.984
<i>To have bitten off the matter with a smile.</i>

238
00:28:42.009 --> 00:28:44.987
<i>To have squeezed the universe into a ball</i>

239
00:28:45.012 --> 00:28:48.469
<i>To roll it toward some
overwhelming question.</i>

240
00:28:48.494 --> 00:28:52.942
<i>To say: “I am Lazarus. come from the dead.</i>

241
00:28:52.967 --> 00:28:57.275
<i>Come back to tell you all.
I shall tell you all”—</i>

242
00:28:57.300 --> 00:29:00.688
<i>If one. settling a pillow by her head.</i>

243
00:29:00.713 --> 00:29:04.595
<i>Should say:
“That is not what I meant at all;</i>

244
00:29:04.627 --> 00:29:07.112
<i> That is not it. at all.”</i>

245
00:29:07.641 --> 00:29:08.875
Excuse me?

246
00:29:10.387 --> 00:29:11.670
Excuse me?

247
00:29:39.345 --> 00:29:40.641
Hello?

248
00:29:41.948 --> 00:29:43.159
Hello.

249
00:30:42.844 --> 00:30:44.981
There's an old woman at school today.

250
00:30:45.717 --> 00:30:47.676
And she's staring at me.

251
00:30:49.213 --> 00:30:51.102
It was like she was following me.

252
00:30:52.281 --> 00:30:53.720
Did you know her?

253
00:30:53.976 --> 00:30:56.032
No. but she freaked me out.

254
00:30:57.359 --> 00:30:59.282
I didn't go back to class.

255
00:31:00.444 --> 00:31:02.320
Did she say something to you?

256
00:31:06.833 --> 00:31:08.543
Hugh told me that.

257
00:31:08.787 --> 00:31:10.859
He passed it on to me.

258
00:31:12.482 --> 00:31:14.791
He said it was going to follow me.

259
00:31:15.332 --> 00:31:17.888
That's all bullshit.
Jamie.

260
00:31:21.066 --> 00:31:22.609
Yeah. I know.

261
00:31:24.534 --> 00:31:27.143
What exactly is suppose to be
following you?

262
00:31:29.050 --> 00:31:30.459
I don't know.

263
00:31:31.622 --> 00:31:33.184
You should tell mom what you saw.

264
00:31:33.209 --> 00:31:34.455
No.

265
00:31:35.352 --> 00:31:36.896
Jay.
I'm worried about you.

266
00:31:37.935 --> 00:31:40.942
I could.. stay over tonight.
If to make you feel any better.

267
00:31:40.967 --> 00:31:42.120
- No.
- No.

268
00:31:42.145 --> 00:31:43.476
Sleep on the couch
or something.

269
00:31:43.501 --> 00:31:44.573
